frameDefinitions: In the course of history, an Event or Entity is taken to have importance or significance.

A Behavior, attributed to an Evaluee, conforms with or is heavily influenced by a popular trend or practice, often in the realm of fashion, design, though extending social and interactional behavior in general.
In this frame, a Resource_controller is judged by a Judge (who is usually implicit)  according to how freely they allow the Recipient access to their Resource.
This frame contains words for individuals as viewed in terms of their age.
This frame contains words that denote Kinship relations.
A Stimulus serves to bring about an emotion of mental stimulation in an Experiencer.
frameExamples: Throughout the campaign activists have <t>made</t> financial <t>history</t> as one by one major corporations have yielded to protester power
Wearing flowered brocaded silks was <t>fashionable</t> in the first few years of the decade.
You will not easily find a more <t>absorbing</t> box-set of piano discs.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the event which occurs to create history.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> which is trendy.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged to conform to some degree with popular fashion with respect to his or her behavior.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Behavior</fen> is trendy or fashionable.
The location where the <fen>Behavior</fen> is trendy..
The Resource_Controller is the individual who controls access to the Resource.
The Resource_controller controls the Recipient's access to the Resource.
The <fen>Recipient</fen> is the individual or individuals who receive or should receive the <fen>Resource</fen> from the <fen>Resource_controller</fen>.
The Behavior is an action of the Resource_controller which is judged to be generous or stingy.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which indicates the character of the <fen>Resource_controller</fen>.
The human being of a certain age.
The <fen>Age</fen> is the length of time the <fen>Person</fen> has been alive.
The person who fills the role named by the Kinship term with respect to the <fen>Ego</fen>.
The person from whose perspective the Kinship relationship is defined.
The combination of <fen>Alter</fen> and <fen>Ego</fen> together.
The <fen>Experiencer</fen> is the person or sentient entity that experiences or feels the emotions.
The <fen>Stimulus</fen> is the person, event, or state of affairs that evokes the emotional response in the <fen>Experiencer</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Experiencer</fen>  can be described as having said emotion.
listRoleExamples: Surprising, Dad was stingy <fex>with his inheritance</fex>.
Mr. Burns is extremely miserly <fex>towards his employees</fex>.
It was generous of Jim <fex>to have us over for dinner</fex>.

sourceCandidateSpans.text: the Church of the Latter Day Saints
